1
00:00:46,129 --> 00:00:51,801
FRANKLY SPEAKING

2
00:00:53,636 --> 00:00:58,850
-Toady, toady, I'll give you an old house
-Toady, toady, I'll give you an old house

3
00:00:58,933 --> 00:01:01,603
-Give me a new house
-Give me a new house

4
00:01:01,686 --> 00:01:06,816
Toady, toady, I'll give you an old house

5
00:01:10,779 --> 00:01:13,865
We will build you a house

6
00:01:13,948 --> 00:01:15,158
Mom.

7
00:01:16,993 --> 00:01:18,328
It's raining.

8
00:01:18,912 --> 00:01:21,372
-What? Is it?
-Let's go home.

9
00:01:21,456 --> 00:01:24,834
Those scary men must've left by now.

10
00:01:25,543 --> 00:01:28,546
Ki-baek, how about we sing the song
just two more times?

11
00:01:29,255 --> 00:01:32,217
Dad will come and get us once they leave.

12
00:01:34,260 --> 00:01:35,887
I'm a blue belt.

13
00:01:35,970 --> 00:01:38,640
If you get scared, I can protect you.

14
00:01:40,350 --> 00:01:44,270
No. If you see those scary men again,
pretend you don't know them.

15
00:01:44,896 --> 00:01:48,233
If you ever run into them,
just tell them you do not know me or Dad.

16
00:01:49,359 --> 00:01:51,319
But lying is bad.

17
00:01:56,157 --> 00:01:59,702
Lying isn't always bad, Ki-baek.

18
00:02:00,495 --> 00:02:05,416
If you have to lie to protect me
and your brother, it's not bad.

19
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:07,418
You're a big brother, Ki-baek.

20
00:02:08,419 --> 00:02:09,796
You can do that, right?

21
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:13,383
Yes!

22
00:02:15,468 --> 00:02:17,345
At first, it started with a white lie.

23
00:02:17,428 --> 00:02:20,223
My parents are very busy, so I don't think

24
00:02:20,306 --> 00:02:22,559
they can attend
the parent-teacher conference.

25
00:02:22,642 --> 00:02:24,352
It wasn't even about anything big.

26
00:02:24,435 --> 00:02:26,104
Your mom called.

27
00:02:26,688 --> 00:02:29,232
She told me she and your dad work
in the countryside.

28
00:02:29,315 --> 00:02:30,900
She was very worried.

29
00:02:32,193 --> 00:02:36,072
I told her to put her worries to rest
because you're so good at everything.

30
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:38,575
From your tuition fees
to your lunch money,

31
00:02:38,658 --> 00:02:40,577
there are ways to get practical help…

32
00:02:41,411 --> 00:02:44,080
Jesus, that was
a long-ass counseling session.

33
00:02:44,164 --> 00:02:46,541
Hey, top student.
What is this, special treatment?

34
00:02:47,167 --> 00:02:48,001
Let's go.

35
00:02:48,084 --> 00:02:50,503
By the way, Ki-baek,
is it true your tutor tells you

36
00:02:50,587 --> 00:02:51,880
what to expect on every test?

37
00:02:51,963 --> 00:02:53,923
This punk will never tell you.

38
00:02:54,007 --> 00:02:55,592
I think he also goes
to a cram school in secret.

39
00:02:57,051 --> 00:03:00,138
I either didn't correct
people's false assumptions about me…

40
00:03:01,890 --> 00:03:03,016
Hey, newbie.

41
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,810
Where do you live?

42
00:03:06,477 --> 00:03:08,229
I live in this area.

43
00:03:08,313 --> 00:03:10,773
You do? Where?

44
00:03:11,900 --> 00:03:13,026
Over there.

45
00:03:13,568 --> 00:03:16,446
Nice. Do you live with your parents?

46
00:03:16,529 --> 00:03:19,949
No, my parents have their own place.

47
00:03:20,033 --> 00:03:21,743
Where do they live? Gangnam?

48
00:03:23,036 --> 00:03:24,203
I knew it.

49
00:03:24,287 --> 00:03:27,040
I thought you looked like you came
from money, you know?

50
00:03:27,123 --> 00:03:28,625
Nice.

51
00:03:28,708 --> 00:03:32,003
I just gave people
the answer they wanted to hear.

52
00:03:32,086 --> 00:03:33,963
-Bye.
-Did you go to school in this area?

53
00:03:56,486 --> 00:03:57,528
Are you heading out?

54
00:03:58,154 --> 00:04:00,698
I bought another bed.
Stop being stubborn and just use it.

55
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:05,912
I'm already so grateful that you let me
crash here from time to time.

56
00:04:06,704 --> 00:04:08,873
I'll take care
of this month's maintenance fees then.

57
00:04:08,957 --> 00:04:12,168
The maintenance fees here are
way more than your monthly salary.

58
00:04:12,835 --> 00:04:17,215
Just look after my car and this place
when I have to work abroad, okay?

59
00:04:22,553 --> 00:04:25,723
You're hosting the news next week.
You need to look dashing.

60
00:04:25,807 --> 00:04:28,017
This is a bit much.
I'm still new, you know.

61
00:04:28,101 --> 00:04:31,229
You should wear expensive clothes
so you can have it easier at work.

62
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:33,398
The office is like a battlefield.

63
00:04:33,481 --> 00:04:36,109
Wear good armor,
and no one will dare to mess with you.

64
00:04:36,192 --> 00:04:37,944
Everyone will want to be your friend.

65
00:04:38,027 --> 00:04:40,113
Call it the art
of protecting yourself, socially.

66
00:04:41,030 --> 00:04:42,031
All right?

67
00:04:42,949 --> 00:04:46,953
Swallowing what you want to say
and saying what others want to hear.

68
00:04:49,747 --> 00:04:52,792
I mean, that's not a bad lie, right?

69
00:04:54,168 --> 00:05:01,009
THE ART OF PROTECTING YOURSELF

70
00:05:01,092 --> 00:05:04,679
EPISODE 3:
THE ART OF PROTECTING YOUR HEART

71
00:05:04,762 --> 00:05:06,097
Mr. Song Ki-baek!

72
00:05:07,890 --> 00:05:08,891
Ki-baek!

73
00:05:16,899 --> 00:05:18,943
What just happened? Am I hurt?

74
00:05:19,027 --> 00:05:21,029
Am I alive right now? What is this?

75
00:05:22,822 --> 00:05:26,034
Ms. On! Are you all right? Are you hurt?

76
00:05:26,117 --> 00:05:28,202
Are you alive? I mean, are you okay?

77
00:05:28,286 --> 00:05:32,081
I said it was dangerous.
I told you to stay away. We nearly died!

78
00:05:32,749 --> 00:05:34,125
Have you gone totally insane?

79
00:05:34,208 --> 00:05:35,501
What did you say?

80
00:05:35,585 --> 00:05:38,296
-Have you gone totally insane? Get a grip!
-What?

81
00:05:38,379 --> 00:05:39,797
You can't seem to snap out of it.

82
00:05:39,881 --> 00:05:42,884
Whenever I see you like this, I feel bad
because I feel like it's my fault.

83
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:45,011
God, why are you being like this?

84
00:05:47,972 --> 00:05:49,307
Well, I mean…

85
00:05:49,974 --> 00:05:52,935
Why did you try to jump into the water?

86
00:05:53,519 --> 00:05:56,522
I had no intention of jumping, whatsoever.

87
00:05:57,106 --> 00:06:01,611
That's why I said it was dangerous
and told you to stay away, numerous times.

88
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:03,613
Because of you, we both slipped and fell!

89
00:06:03,696 --> 00:06:05,406
We nearly died!

90
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:08,409
Also, you asked me if I'd gone insane.

91
00:06:08,493 --> 00:06:10,286
What I have is called disinhibition.

92
00:06:10,369 --> 00:06:13,206
It means I can't control
my emotions or actions.

93
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:15,875
I'm sick! That is what the doctor said!

94
00:06:17,043 --> 00:06:18,753
Is it very serious?

95
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:22,298
Do they have to open your skull?

96
00:06:22,381 --> 00:06:25,927
My head is about to split in half
because of you. Do you hear me?

97
00:06:26,010 --> 00:06:27,261
-What?
-Fine.

98
00:06:27,345 --> 00:06:29,680
If it's difficult for you
to pretend not to know me

99
00:06:29,764 --> 00:06:32,934
because of your personality,
let's just be total strangers.

100
00:06:33,017 --> 00:06:35,895
Don't follow me. Really, don't.

101
00:06:36,604 --> 00:06:38,022
Seriously.

102
00:06:43,361 --> 00:06:44,862
What a freak.

103
00:06:53,287 --> 00:06:54,122
Where is he?

104
00:06:54,205 --> 00:06:56,415
My phone got all wet
and isn't even working now.

105
00:06:57,416 --> 00:06:58,626
God, Yoon Ji-hu.

106
00:07:02,964 --> 00:07:06,092
What is this? What a mess.

107
00:07:06,592 --> 00:07:08,219
Seriously, what is this?

108
00:07:09,804 --> 00:07:12,140
But I saved someone's life…

109
00:07:13,516 --> 00:07:14,934
Whatever.

110
00:07:16,978 --> 00:07:20,773
This is nuts.
My car seats will get all ruined.

111
00:07:21,983 --> 00:07:22,984
Damn it.

112
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:27,155
Huh?

113
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:33,661
What?

114
00:07:34,162 --> 00:07:35,163
What now?

115
00:07:36,747 --> 00:07:37,874
The car's gone.

116
00:07:38,499 --> 00:07:40,668
The guy I came with
vanished without a trace.

117
00:07:42,753 --> 00:07:44,255
Okay, so?

118
00:07:44,338 --> 00:07:46,549
Well, practically everyone
in the country knows me,

119
00:07:46,632 --> 00:07:49,343
thanks to the unsavory incident
that happened recently,

120
00:07:49,427 --> 00:07:52,180
so I cannot use public transit.

121
00:07:53,139 --> 00:07:55,766
What are you, a top-tier celebrity?

122
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,811
So?

123
00:07:59,937 --> 00:08:01,230
Give me a ride.

124
00:08:02,148 --> 00:08:04,692
You know it's absurd, right?
The two of us and this situation.

125
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:07,653
Let me get a ride, please.

126
00:08:11,073 --> 00:08:12,158
Fine, get in.

127
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:15,828
Wait!

128
00:08:15,912 --> 00:08:18,623
It's brand-new. I haven't even made
my first payment yet.

129
00:08:18,706 --> 00:08:21,250
Are you going to push the car
down the road instead of driving?

130
00:08:21,334 --> 00:08:25,004
Well, I would if I could, but I can't…

131
00:08:26,005 --> 00:08:27,006
That's right.

132
00:08:34,889 --> 00:08:35,806
Korean wrestling.

133
00:08:36,474 --> 00:08:37,308
What?

134
00:08:37,391 --> 00:08:39,560
I mean, I'm good at it.

135
00:08:40,811 --> 00:08:41,896
This won't do.

136
00:08:42,563 --> 00:08:44,482
Oh, yes. This will work.

137
00:08:46,609 --> 00:08:47,902
I can't wear this.

138
00:08:47,985 --> 00:08:49,362
Right, you can't wear this.

139
00:08:49,445 --> 00:08:50,696
That won't even fit.

140
00:08:50,780 --> 00:08:53,658
I've got something for you.
I have something you can wear.

141
00:09:07,964 --> 00:09:10,758
MEN ON THE RUN

142
00:09:13,719 --> 00:09:16,597
I thought you guys only played ball games
on Men on the Run.

143
00:09:16,681 --> 00:09:19,183
Well, we played all sorts of games
in the early days.

144
00:09:21,811 --> 00:09:25,439
Why do the youngsters
these days like cropped tops so much?

145
00:09:25,523 --> 00:09:26,524
Isn't it uncomfortable?

146
00:09:28,651 --> 00:09:31,112
Let's wear our own clothes.
I'll pay for you to wash your car.

147
00:09:32,154 --> 00:09:34,991
They're soaked in salt water.
It won't wash out.

148
00:09:35,074 --> 00:09:36,951
Just find your own way back then.

149
00:09:37,493 --> 00:09:39,996
What kind of psycho
walks around like this?

150
00:09:40,079 --> 00:09:41,080
FULL OF LOVE

151
00:09:41,163 --> 00:09:43,708
Do you know what I had to go through
to find this costume?

152
00:09:43,791 --> 00:09:45,334
Here, have some water.

153
00:09:45,418 --> 00:09:46,794
-Oh, hello.
-Hi.

154
00:09:47,962 --> 00:09:50,715
Isn't it about time
you took off that spandex suit?

155
00:09:50,798 --> 00:09:52,383
You're supposed to be
the ideal son-in-law.

156
00:09:52,466 --> 00:09:55,678
What put me on the map when I was trying
to decide between music or variety TV?

157
00:09:55,761 --> 00:09:59,765
This saved me from nearly ruining myself
while trying to keep up with Young-woong.

158
00:09:59,849 --> 00:10:01,183
-Do I look cute?
-Sure do.

159
00:10:01,267 --> 00:10:03,936
Are you going to take on
Director Jang's new show on GBS?

160
00:10:04,020 --> 00:10:05,938
-Nope.
-What about the MBS pilot?

161
00:10:06,022 --> 00:10:07,148
No, I won't do it.

162
00:10:08,399 --> 00:10:12,361
I see you're busy posting photos
of yourself in that spandex suit.

163
00:10:12,445 --> 00:10:14,447
Oh, "On Woo-ju, JBC"?

164
00:10:14,530 --> 00:10:16,574
"On Woo-ju"? You mean the writer?

165
00:10:17,116 --> 00:10:20,077
Is she doing a JBC show?
Did they confirm a time slot for it?

166
00:10:20,161 --> 00:10:21,912
They will if I do the show.

167
00:10:21,996 --> 00:10:25,916
You're expressing your interest in a show
that hasn't even been confirmed yet?

168
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:27,835
-I need to put this wig on you.
-Okay.

169
00:10:27,918 --> 00:10:30,796
Just wait. I'll explain
what's going on once I know for sure.

170
00:10:34,550 --> 00:10:36,344
Ms. On, are you all right?

171
00:10:37,803 --> 00:10:40,514
Your face looks pale.
It looks blue, actually.

172
00:10:40,598 --> 00:10:41,724
I'm fine.

173
00:10:42,850 --> 00:10:45,770
Hang in there. There's no traffic,
so we'll get home in no time.

174
00:10:47,104 --> 00:10:51,317
Anyway, why did you go up there?
I don't think you were trying to drown.

175
00:10:53,027 --> 00:10:54,153
Just because.

176
00:10:55,988 --> 00:10:59,950
Normally, I never do things for no reason.

177
00:11:00,534 --> 00:11:03,537
But these days, I can't help it.

178
00:11:04,705 --> 00:11:08,209
I remember thinking to myself,
"I want to look down at the ocean."

179
00:11:08,292 --> 00:11:11,629
The next thing I knew,
I was already climbing the rocks.

180
00:11:16,634 --> 00:11:18,469
Ms. On, are you really okay?

181
00:11:18,552 --> 00:11:19,553
I'm fine.

182
00:11:19,637 --> 00:11:22,515
I don't have indemnity insurance.
I can't get into an accident.

183
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,477
Let's pull over onto the shoulder.

184
00:11:26,560 --> 00:11:29,605
Yes, right here. Slow down.
That's it. Careful.

185
00:11:32,316 --> 00:11:33,776
I'm really okay.

186
00:11:33,859 --> 00:11:36,821
Do you accumulate points
for repeatedly saying that you're okay?

187
00:11:36,904 --> 00:11:40,574
You keep saying you're okay
when it's obvious that you're not.

188
00:11:40,658 --> 00:11:43,285
But you keep saying, "I'm not okay,"
I mean, "I'm okay"?

189
00:11:44,495 --> 00:11:46,622
Huh? Ms. On.

190
00:11:47,832 --> 00:11:49,792
Ms. On Woo-ju?

191
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:51,544
What?

192
00:11:51,627 --> 00:11:52,711
Hey…

193
00:11:52,795 --> 00:11:54,422
Ms. On Woo-ju. Hey…

194
00:12:01,971 --> 00:12:04,390
Help! Over here!

195
00:12:04,473 --> 00:12:06,016
We need help!

196
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:07,977
Sir, open your eyes.

197
00:12:08,561 --> 00:12:11,230
-What happened?
-He suddenly collapsed while on a trip.

198
00:12:15,609 --> 00:12:18,362
Man, she clearly isn't okay.

199
00:12:20,364 --> 00:12:21,532
Excuse me.

200
00:12:22,658 --> 00:12:25,453
-My little brother is…
-Hold on. One moment.

201
00:12:26,912 --> 00:12:27,997
Are you all right?

202
00:13:05,075 --> 00:13:06,410
Oh, you woke up.

203
00:13:06,494 --> 00:13:09,288
What's with the blanket and the mask?

204
00:13:10,039 --> 00:13:11,916
I don't want anyone to recognize me.

205
00:13:14,543 --> 00:13:16,337
Anyway, who's that boy?

206
00:13:16,420 --> 00:13:17,796
I don't know.

207
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,049
Hey, worry about yourself first.

208
00:13:20,674 --> 00:13:22,510
I'm okay.

209
00:13:23,761 --> 00:13:25,429
Help!

210
00:13:25,513 --> 00:13:27,473
He's not breathing.

211
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:29,600
Help!

212
00:13:30,684 --> 00:13:32,436
Please save him.

213
00:13:33,020 --> 00:13:34,980
Hey, kid. Are you all right?

214
00:13:42,238 --> 00:13:44,657
They told me to wait until Mom gets here,

215
00:13:45,449 --> 00:13:47,284
but my brother is sick.

216
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:56,627
Once upon a time, a famous man
named Confucius said this.

217
00:13:56,710 --> 00:14:01,257
"When in need, birds can peck the grain,
dogs can bite people

218
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:06,136
and people can lie."

219
00:14:07,179 --> 00:14:10,015
-Pardon me?
-What do you think you should do

220
00:14:10,516 --> 00:14:12,059
to grab people's attention?

221
00:14:13,477 --> 00:14:14,895
You saw that earlier.

222
00:14:19,984 --> 00:14:21,193
Oh, boy.

223
00:14:26,490 --> 00:14:28,784
You had temporary hypothermia.

224
00:14:28,868 --> 00:14:31,370
We brought your temperature
back up to the normal range.

225
00:14:31,453 --> 00:14:33,622
You can go home once the drip is finished.

226
00:14:34,248 --> 00:14:35,499
Thank you.

227
00:14:41,422 --> 00:14:44,967
I really am okay now.
You can go. Get going.

228
00:14:45,050 --> 00:14:48,512
Hey, you need to lie down.

229
00:14:50,431 --> 00:14:52,308
Wait until the drip is finished.

230
00:14:53,809 --> 00:14:54,894
My goodness.

231
00:15:01,859 --> 00:15:04,737
Wow, nice place.

232
00:15:05,779 --> 00:15:09,867
It's your fault that this happened,
so I won't thank you for the ride.

233
00:15:10,743 --> 00:15:12,369
Can you drive yourself home?

234
00:15:12,995 --> 00:15:14,538
Oh, sure.

235
00:15:18,042 --> 00:15:19,209
You can go.

236
00:15:25,591 --> 00:15:28,260
You had hypothermia
and had to go to the emergency room.

237
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:30,804
Do you not eat? What are you, a kid?

238
00:15:31,305 --> 00:15:33,057
You're as light as a feather.

239
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:34,892
Cover your stomach. It's cold.

240
00:15:37,645 --> 00:15:38,646
I'm off.

241
00:15:39,563 --> 00:15:40,689
Wait, Mr. Song Ki-baek.

242
00:15:42,775 --> 00:15:44,151
Thanks for your help earlier.

243
00:16:05,005 --> 00:16:06,966
ANNOUNCER SONG KI-BAEK'S
FIRST NEWS SEGMENT

244
00:16:16,684 --> 00:16:20,312
The system will undergo a total makeover
to allow children's meal tickets

245
00:16:20,396 --> 00:16:22,481
to be used at any eatery.

246
00:16:22,564 --> 00:16:26,193
Currently, children's meal tickets can
only be used at registered eateries,

247
00:16:26,276 --> 00:16:30,447
which are mainly limited
to convenience stores.

248
00:16:30,531 --> 00:16:33,951
The City of Gyeongmun has announced
that the tickets can be used

249
00:16:34,034 --> 00:16:38,789
at any place that accepts credit cards
once the change takes effect.

250
00:16:38,872 --> 00:16:41,250
The tickets are issued
for children under the age of 18

251
00:16:41,333 --> 00:16:43,127
who are likely to be food insecure.

252
00:16:43,210 --> 00:16:45,462
Inflation will be taken
into consideration in…

253
