It's what youngsters say these days.
You need to learn these things.

317
00:21:42,968 --> 00:21:44,261
It feels so damp in here.

318
00:21:44,761 --> 00:21:46,138
What are they, moles?

319
00:21:51,268 --> 00:21:55,939
Anyway, speaking of which,
we're understaffed and--

320
00:21:57,691 --> 00:21:59,192
Bonjour!

321
00:22:01,111 --> 00:22:02,571
Hello.

322
00:22:05,574 --> 00:22:08,160
My goodness, Ha-young is here.

323
00:22:11,872 --> 00:22:14,041
I thought we were meeting tomorrow.

324
00:22:14,124 --> 00:22:16,168
-You came a day early.
-Yeah.

325
00:22:18,837 --> 00:22:19,880
It's been a while.

326
00:22:20,797 --> 00:22:22,341
Yes. Hi.

327
00:22:26,428 --> 00:22:29,806
You're my adorable honey bunny

328
00:22:29,890 --> 00:22:32,976
I'm your raccoon

329
00:22:33,060 --> 00:22:35,312
I'm Na Yu-jeong, your beauty manager.

330
00:22:35,395 --> 00:22:36,605
Here, take one.

331
00:22:36,688 --> 00:22:39,316
I do house calls too.

332
00:22:39,399 --> 00:22:41,860
Give me a call.
They're skincare products. The best!

333
00:22:41,943 --> 00:22:43,570
Give me a call.

334
00:22:43,653 --> 00:22:46,114
You rock, lady. Stay healthy.

335
00:22:47,115 --> 00:22:50,077
Wherever we go, we're stars

336
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:52,370
-We're Mr. and…
-Ms. Popular!

337
00:22:52,454 --> 00:22:55,290
-Let's hold hands and have some fun
-Na Yu-jeong, beauty manager.

338
00:22:55,373 --> 00:22:57,876
Spin, spin, spin around and look cool

339
00:22:57,959 --> 00:22:58,794
Look cool!

340
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:01,963
Sparkle, sparkle, I see no one but you

341
00:23:02,047 --> 00:23:05,383
Hop, hop, my adorable lady

342
00:23:05,467 --> 00:23:08,637
Come to me, softly and quietly

343
00:23:08,720 --> 00:23:11,807
Stop drinking that thing
and pack some rice cakes.

344
00:23:12,390 --> 00:23:13,517
Rice cakes? Why?

345
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:17,395
This is Ki-baek's favorite rice cake.
He likes it steamed and grilled.

346
00:23:17,479 --> 00:23:19,147
He'd rather have this than rice.

347
00:23:20,732 --> 00:23:23,276
Should I call him to come
and pick up the rice cakes?

348
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:25,070
Make way, all of you, here I come

349
00:23:25,153 --> 00:23:27,864
Hello, I'm Na Yu-jeong,
your beauty manager.

350
00:23:41,628 --> 00:23:42,671
Thanks.

351
00:23:44,256 --> 00:23:45,715
-Are you the newbie?
-Hello.

352
00:23:45,799 --> 00:23:47,134
-Nice to meet you.
-Likewise.

353
00:23:47,217 --> 00:23:49,469
You said their pre-recording was today.
You can go.

354
00:23:49,553 --> 00:23:50,804
Oh, thank you.

355
00:23:50,887 --> 00:23:53,223
Being supportive
of the newbie's fan activities?

356
00:23:53,306 --> 00:23:55,934
I heard you were in a tight spot.
Guess that's not the case.

357
00:23:57,644 --> 00:23:58,895
I-na, you can get going.

358
00:23:58,979 --> 00:24:00,313
-It's okay.
-Thank you.

359
00:24:01,439 --> 00:24:02,858
Well…

360
00:24:03,775 --> 00:24:07,279
Ha-young is joining the team.

361
00:24:07,362 --> 00:24:10,407
Chief went through hoops to persuade her
as soon as she returned to Korea.

362
00:24:12,951 --> 00:24:15,537
Woo-ju as our head writer
and Ha-young to back her up.

363
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:17,330
Now we have nothing to worry about.

364
00:24:19,916 --> 00:24:22,294
After my divorce,
I lived in Cali for a year,

365
00:24:22,377 --> 00:24:25,630
then in Paris the following year,
so has it been about two years?

366
00:24:26,173 --> 00:24:27,007
Yeah.

367
00:24:27,090 --> 00:24:30,635
You haven't changed one bit.
You still have such fair skin.

368
00:24:31,595 --> 00:24:33,847
You must've spent
all your time planning shows.

369
00:24:33,930 --> 00:24:37,184
What are you talking about?
It's because I use an expensive sunscreen.

370
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:40,520
Haven't you been watching TV?
I've worked on a number of shows.

371
00:24:41,229 --> 00:24:44,441
Better keep up. You'll lose your touch.

372
00:24:45,025 --> 00:24:46,985
I only watch shows that do well.

373
00:24:47,068 --> 00:24:50,655
I feel like my brain is rotting
when I watch unpopular shows.

374
00:24:54,618 --> 00:24:56,828
I was so happy for you
when you left the team

375
00:24:56,912 --> 00:24:59,748
to jump on the opportunity
to work as a head writer.

376
00:24:59,831 --> 00:25:03,335
Nice to see you after just two years.
It's like my runaway child is back.

377
00:25:03,418 --> 00:25:06,755
And that runaway child can pull
the family out of the gutter now.

378
00:25:07,631 --> 00:25:09,132
Who is she, really?

379
00:25:10,759 --> 00:25:11,801
Writer Lee Ha-young.

380
00:25:12,719 --> 00:25:15,388
-But who is she?
-The legendary newbie.

381
00:25:15,472 --> 00:25:19,059
The uncontrollable, unimaginable,

382
00:25:20,143 --> 00:25:21,144
and the worst newbie.

383
00:25:21,228 --> 00:25:22,312
HOMETOWN REPORT AT NOON

384
00:25:22,395 --> 00:25:23,563
Gwangju in Gyeonggi?

385
00:25:23,647 --> 00:25:25,190
TV CREW

386
00:25:25,273 --> 00:25:27,359
It's Gwangju in Jeolla.
How could you confuse them?

387
00:25:27,442 --> 00:25:29,236
You said you scouted a school there.

388
00:25:29,319 --> 00:25:32,781
There's a school
with the exact same name in Gyeonggi.

389
00:25:32,864 --> 00:25:34,282
What should we do?

390
00:25:34,366 --> 00:25:36,451
Call city hall and ask if we can shoot.

391
00:25:36,534 --> 00:25:39,371
Find out if we can do
something like a pottery experience.

392
00:25:39,955 --> 00:25:41,623
Stay out of the senior writers' sight.

393
00:25:42,207 --> 00:25:45,418
If someone says something to you,
just keep talking on the phone.

394
00:25:45,961 --> 00:25:47,128
Hey, hide.

395
00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:50,966
That's how the legend began.

396
00:25:52,801 --> 00:25:55,720
What should I do? You see, this is…

397
00:25:55,804 --> 00:25:57,013
Woo-ju.

398
00:25:59,349 --> 00:26:00,308
Woo-ju!

399
00:26:00,392 --> 00:26:02,018
-Pour them in here.
-Okay.

400
00:26:02,102 --> 00:26:03,270
Sorry, we'll be quick.

401
00:26:03,895 --> 00:26:05,438
-Hurry up and pour.
-Okay.

402
00:26:05,522 --> 00:26:06,898
Hey, Ha-young.

403
00:26:08,566 --> 00:26:10,735
What? You forgot their passports?

404
00:26:10,819 --> 00:26:12,529
You've got to be kidding me.

405
00:26:14,864 --> 00:26:16,700
Woo-ju had just graduated
from newbie status,

406
00:26:16,783 --> 00:26:20,203
so she had a lot on her plate too,
but Ha-young was really something.

407
00:26:20,287 --> 00:26:24,249
She always had Ha-young right by her side,
like a mother hen nurturing its egg.

408
00:26:24,332 --> 00:26:25,166
It's not that heavy.

409
00:26:25,250 --> 00:26:27,669
But if they struggled
and learned things together,

410
00:26:27,752 --> 00:26:29,879
shouldn't they be pretty close?

411
00:26:29,963 --> 00:26:31,214
What's with those two?

412
00:26:31,298 --> 00:26:34,759
Woo-ju trained Ha-young so well

413
00:26:35,468 --> 00:26:38,346
that Ha-young got an offer
to be another team's head writer.

414
00:26:38,430 --> 00:26:40,932
Woo-ju was getting ready
to debut as a head writer too.

415
00:26:41,016 --> 00:26:43,393
Not long after she had assembled the team,

416
00:26:43,476 --> 00:26:44,811
Ha-young suddenly left.

417
00:26:45,729 --> 00:26:49,316
When Ha-young was a subwriter,
she was a legend in a different sense.

418
00:26:50,025 --> 00:26:52,736
She had a knack for casting
and had brilliant ideas.

419
00:26:54,863 --> 00:26:56,906
Let's get along, okay?

420
00:26:56,990 --> 00:27:00,118
If I were Woo-ju, seeing her again
would make me uncomfortable.

421
00:27:00,201 --> 00:27:01,995
Will Woo-ju be all right?

422
00:27:09,336 --> 00:27:11,838
Hey, have you grown taller?

423
00:27:13,048 --> 00:27:14,674
I've got a casting meeting.

424
00:27:14,758 --> 00:27:17,135
Oh, they've agreed to meet you?

425
00:27:17,218 --> 00:27:19,179
Yes, of course. Who'd turn me down?

426
00:27:21,348 --> 00:27:22,891
Have some coffee before you go.

427
00:27:29,898 --> 00:27:31,149
My ears feel clogged.

428
00:27:31,232 --> 00:27:34,819
This is way too high for me.
I feel like I'm getting motion sickness.

429
00:27:35,653 --> 00:27:37,364
I told you we should call first.

430
00:27:37,447 --> 00:27:39,866
The security guard always treats us
like we're solicitors.

431
00:27:39,949 --> 00:27:42,118
My goodness. Be quiet, will you?

432
00:27:44,245 --> 00:27:46,373
What? He could be home now.

433
00:27:46,456 --> 00:27:49,250
That's exactly why.

434
00:27:49,334 --> 00:27:51,086
Do you think he'd want to see us?

435
00:27:51,169 --> 00:27:52,962
He has a lot of pride, you know.

436
00:27:53,046 --> 00:27:54,255
Just hang this here.

437
00:27:54,339 --> 00:27:57,801
You want to leave without seeing him
after coming all this way?

438
00:28:06,810 --> 00:28:09,854
What are you doing?
You can't see anything through that hole.

439
00:28:34,379 --> 00:28:35,380
He took it.

440
00:28:35,880 --> 00:28:36,881
Let's go.

441
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:48,309
I won't even eat this stuff.
Why do they always…

442
00:28:48,393 --> 00:28:49,728
This is good.

