462
00:29:57,504 --> 00:29:59,130
Why do you ask?

463
00:30:00,548 --> 00:30:01,549
Huh?

464
00:30:02,050 --> 00:30:03,259
What's with this guy?

465
00:30:04,844 --> 00:30:06,888
Yeah, I'm coming. I'm on my way now.

466
00:30:06,971 --> 00:30:09,098
Just tell them
I'm running a few minutes behind.

467
00:30:09,182 --> 00:30:10,099
Hey, Mr. Kwak.

468
00:30:10,183 --> 00:30:12,477
-Gosh, what the--
-Finally, I get to see you.

469
00:30:12,560 --> 00:30:14,354
Hey, you're still here?

470
00:30:14,437 --> 00:30:17,106
Come on. I waited for you, as I should.
Hey, Mr. Kwak.

471
00:30:17,190 --> 00:30:19,859
We've been through
thick and thin together.

472
00:30:19,943 --> 00:30:21,152
Could you help me, please?

473
00:30:22,070 --> 00:30:27,075
I'll accommodate your schedule, pay,
food preferences, mood and lifestyle.

474
00:30:27,158 --> 00:30:28,535
What do you say? Are you in?

475
00:30:29,410 --> 00:30:30,411
Listen, Woo-ju.

476
00:30:30,495 --> 00:30:32,789
If I want to live, I must eat and poop.

477
00:30:32,872 --> 00:30:35,041
I don't eat
because I have no time to poop.

478
00:30:35,124 --> 00:30:36,751
And I can't poop because I don't eat.

479
00:30:36,835 --> 00:30:38,586
I won't take up a lot of your time.

480
00:30:38,670 --> 00:30:41,089
Ms. On, I hear you're having a hard time.

481
00:30:42,048 --> 00:30:44,425
You haven't even secured
a time slot for it yet.

482
00:30:45,260 --> 00:30:47,887
You expect me to do
We Live Together just to help you?

483
00:30:47,971 --> 00:30:49,389
No, no way.

484
00:30:49,472 --> 00:30:50,890
I want to live at my place.

485
00:30:50,974 --> 00:30:52,141
Let's go to my place.

486
00:30:52,225 --> 00:30:54,769
-Hey, come on.
-Writer On Woo-ju.

487
00:30:56,437 --> 00:31:01,234
I came over here to see
if it was really you, and here you are.

488
00:31:01,985 --> 00:31:03,361
-Hey.
-Sorry to interrupt.

489
00:31:03,444 --> 00:31:05,905
You're not interrupting.

490
00:31:06,406 --> 00:31:08,324
You haven't been
in the office for a while.

491
00:31:08,408 --> 00:31:10,451
I'm supposed to have a meal
with the CEO today.

492
00:31:10,535 --> 00:31:11,619
Oh, really?

493
00:31:11,703 --> 00:31:12,745
Anyway, Ms. On.

494
00:31:13,371 --> 00:31:15,248
It's so hard to get a meeting with you.

495
00:31:15,790 --> 00:31:18,209
-Sorry?
-I told you I wanted a casting meeting.

496
00:31:18,877 --> 00:31:20,628
-Well…
-A casting meeting?

497
00:31:21,170 --> 00:31:24,424
Hey, why didn't you tell me?

498
00:31:25,091 --> 00:31:28,094
Hey, Jeong-heon. Woo-ju.
Let's go grab a coffee or something.

499
00:31:28,177 --> 00:31:29,637
No, Mr. Kwak.

500
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:32,640
I get what you're trying to say.
I'll be in touch.

501
00:31:32,724 --> 00:31:35,685
Come on! Hey.
Don't be all business with me.

502
00:31:35,768 --> 00:31:39,564
Drop the "Mr." Just call me Beom. We good?

503
00:31:40,648 --> 00:31:42,901
Beom, I'll be in touch then.

504
00:31:43,443 --> 00:31:44,986
Call me, Woo-ju.

505
00:31:48,072 --> 00:31:50,325
Hey, Jeong-heon.

506
00:31:50,408 --> 00:31:54,662
We're represented by the same agency,
so we'll be like a package deal.

507
00:31:54,746 --> 00:31:56,205
You get the idea, right?

508
00:31:57,540 --> 00:31:58,583
Shall we do it?

509
00:31:59,167 --> 00:32:02,754
But if I'm the main item,
I don't need a freebie to seal the deal.

510
00:32:03,338 --> 00:32:05,798
-What's with you?
-I'll see you around then.

511
00:32:05,882 --> 00:32:07,216
Let's do it!

512
00:32:07,300 --> 00:32:09,427
-That's not even funny. Don't do that.
-Hey, but…

513
00:32:14,265 --> 00:32:15,266
Huh?

514
00:32:19,270 --> 00:32:21,397
Did you call me after a few days

515
00:32:21,481 --> 00:32:23,733
and ask me where I was
to come and find me?

516
00:32:24,233 --> 00:32:26,569
I think I've figured it out.

517
00:32:26,653 --> 00:32:27,654
Figured out what?

518
00:32:27,737 --> 00:32:30,782
That mysterious link
between inhibition and disinhibition?

519
00:32:30,865 --> 00:32:33,159
Do you mind putting it in layman's terms?

520
00:32:35,036 --> 00:32:36,412
Hey, come here.

521
00:32:38,665 --> 00:32:41,584
I'm not in the mood to joke around
with you today.

522
00:32:41,668 --> 00:32:43,670
Well, I'm dead serious right now too.

523
00:32:43,753 --> 00:32:45,713
All right, what's three times six?

524
00:32:48,591 --> 00:32:49,801
Eighteen.

525
00:32:49,884 --> 00:32:50,885
What?

526
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:52,637
I mean, I'm 20…

527
00:32:53,554 --> 00:32:54,931
I'm 40.

528
00:32:56,015 --> 00:32:58,226
I'm 33. Damn it.

529
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:00,061
What the heck are you saying?

530
00:33:00,144 --> 00:33:04,065
Whenever I saw your face in the past,
I got this strong feeling and felt okay.

531
00:33:05,358 --> 00:33:06,818
Was this not the reason?

532
00:33:06,901 --> 00:33:08,361
Why not?

533
00:33:08,444 --> 00:33:10,780
God. Let go, will you?

534
00:33:19,205 --> 00:33:20,331
It's my son-in-law!

535
00:33:20,415 --> 00:33:23,876
Hop, hop, my adorable lady

536
00:33:23,960 --> 00:33:26,879
Why is he your son-in-law?
He's everyone's dream son-in-law.

537
00:33:26,963 --> 00:33:29,090
Goodness, isn't he so cute?

538
00:33:29,173 --> 00:33:30,967
He's well-spoken and a great dancer.

539
00:33:31,050 --> 00:33:33,261
Your daughter works
at a broadcasting station.

540
00:33:33,344 --> 00:33:34,595
Ask her if you can see him.

541
00:33:34,679 --> 00:33:38,558
I asked her to get me his autograph,
and she flat out ignored me.

542
00:33:38,641 --> 00:33:40,351
That brat is such a snob.

543
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:41,436
But you know what?

544
00:33:41,519 --> 00:33:45,440
Every time I see him,
I feel like I know him personally.

545
00:33:45,523 --> 00:33:49,277
He and Ki-baek went
to high school together.

546
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:50,194
-Huh?
-What?

547
00:33:50,278 --> 00:33:51,904
Your forever soul mate

548
00:33:51,988 --> 00:33:55,742
Again? You didn't have to bring anything.

549
00:33:55,825 --> 00:33:58,161
It's nothing compared to
the peaches you gave us.

550
00:33:58,244 --> 00:33:59,412
Anyway, thanks.

551
00:34:02,248 --> 00:34:04,625
-The front gate works now.
-Okay, thanks.

552
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:06,711
Hey, Un-baek.

553
00:34:06,794 --> 00:34:08,379
Did you know that Ki-baek

554
00:34:08,463 --> 00:34:10,882
and Kim Jeong-heon were friends
in high school?

555
00:34:12,341 --> 00:34:13,551
"Friends"?

556
00:34:13,634 --> 00:34:15,178
Here comes your raccoon

557
00:34:15,261 --> 00:34:16,262
I doubt that.

558
00:34:17,597 --> 00:34:19,515
Do you guys know each other?

559
00:34:20,308 --> 00:34:23,269
I believe you said hi to each other
at the award ceremony too.

560
00:34:23,352 --> 00:34:26,314
Oh, we went to high school together.
We're friends.

561
00:34:26,397 --> 00:34:28,691
We just went to the same school.

562
00:34:30,985 --> 00:34:34,822
Back in high school, Ki-baek was
the top student, and he was athletic too.

563
00:34:34,906 --> 00:34:36,407
He was perfect in every way.

564
00:34:37,366 --> 00:34:39,994
Are you talking about yourself?
You were Mr. Perfect.

565
00:34:40,078 --> 00:34:42,497
You were athletic and rich,
and you had lots of friends.

566
00:34:44,123 --> 00:34:45,166
That is true.

567
00:34:45,249 --> 00:34:46,626
Go on and catch up, you two.

568
00:34:46,709 --> 00:34:48,294
-No.
-No, wait.

569
00:34:50,797 --> 00:34:52,090
What are you doing? Let go.

570
00:34:56,803 --> 00:34:58,763
Wait, it's weird.

571
00:35:01,557 --> 00:35:03,810
-Woo-ju.
-Just go. I'm not interested.

572
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:26,541
MADAM ON

573
00:35:31,087 --> 00:35:32,588
HANGUK MILK
STRAWBERRY

574
00:35:40,429 --> 00:35:43,307
I bet you got chewed out again
or something like that.

575
00:35:43,391 --> 00:35:46,352
If you're upset about something,
just sleep it off.

576
00:35:46,435 --> 00:35:48,604
Why do you have to make such a fuss?

577
00:35:48,688 --> 00:35:51,065
Nothing gets resolved
if you just sit around.

578
00:35:51,149 --> 00:35:52,316
I must do something.

579
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:55,778
Then while you're at it, wash these too.

580
00:36:04,537 --> 00:36:06,247
YEON

581
00:36:07,248 --> 00:36:10,168
-What's up?
-Hey, why didn't you tell me?

582
00:36:10,251 --> 00:36:12,461
I hear Kim Jeong-heon has taken the bait.

583
00:36:12,962 --> 00:36:15,548
"Taken the bait"? What is he, a fish?

584
00:36:17,216 --> 00:36:18,467
On Woo-ju.

585
00:36:19,302 --> 00:36:20,511
Hey, Woo-ju.

586
00:36:24,265 --> 00:36:26,309
So you have no interest in me. About that…

587
00:36:29,270 --> 00:36:31,814
-But aren't you here to work?
-Yeah, exactly.

588
00:36:31,898 --> 00:36:34,984
So, why did you have to butt in
and ruin everything?

589
00:36:35,067 --> 00:36:38,362
You think I ruined your project?

590
00:36:40,823 --> 00:36:42,241
I am Kim Jeong-heon, you see.

591
00:36:43,284 --> 00:36:48,789
I'm genuinely interested in your new show
as a show host, not as your ex-boyfriend.

592
00:36:51,584 --> 00:36:53,794
So decide wisely. You're a pro.

593
00:36:58,883 --> 00:37:04,055
I pulled all sorts of antics
to do a good job but got no work done.

594
00:37:05,306 --> 00:37:06,557
I'm so embarrassed.

595
00:37:25,326 --> 00:37:27,828
You can promise me
you'll keep it to yourself, right?

596
00:37:27,912 --> 00:37:31,415
It's crucial that I get to the bottom
of it if I want my job back.

597
00:37:32,083 --> 00:37:35,294
A doctor must keep
his patients' personal info confidential.

598
00:37:36,587 --> 00:37:38,172
But this is no hospital.

599
00:37:38,256 --> 00:37:41,133
I suggest making an outpatient appointment
in the afternoon.

600
00:37:41,217 --> 00:37:43,469
Is it possible though?

601
00:37:43,552 --> 00:37:48,516
You mean, symptoms of disinhibition
suddenly disappearing or returning?

602
00:37:48,599 --> 00:37:51,519
That's right. So I tried to look
for some patterns, but…

603
00:37:51,602 --> 00:37:53,271
Well, that failed.

604
00:37:53,938 --> 00:37:55,982
It could be caused
by an imprinting effect.

605
00:37:56,065 --> 00:37:58,859
If a certain situation
or action at the time of the incident

606
00:37:58,943 --> 00:38:00,736
left a lasting imprint on your mind,

607
00:38:00,820 --> 00:38:05,074
it could turn your symptoms on and off,
like a switch.

608
00:38:05,658 --> 00:38:08,786
So you're saying there's a switch
I don't know about inside my head?

609
00:38:08,869 --> 00:38:10,371
Now I'm even more confused.

610
00:38:12,331 --> 00:38:14,333
Hey, don't do it like that.

611
00:38:15,001 --> 00:38:16,377
Watch me, okay?

612
00:38:16,460 --> 00:38:18,879
-One second.
-Fold it over.

613
00:38:18,963 --> 00:38:21,465
Pick it up using the center point,
then shake it once.

614
00:38:24,218 --> 00:38:28,264
I have a problem staying calm because
I don't know when the symptoms will come.

615
00:38:29,390 --> 00:38:33,894
What if the switch turns on
when I'm at work tomorrow?

616
00:38:34,395 --> 00:38:38,899
It'll be helpful for you
if you can find out what that "switch" is.

617
00:38:38,983 --> 00:38:43,904
For now, let's wait and see how it goes,
while hoping it won't turn on again.

618
00:38:46,615 --> 00:38:47,700
All right.

619
00:38:57,335 --> 00:39:00,504
SONG KI-BAEK

620
00:39:20,107 --> 00:39:21,192
Hello.

621
00:39:21,275 --> 00:39:22,818
-Hello.
-Oh, yes. Hello.

622
00:39:25,363 --> 00:39:27,490
-Hello.
-Oh, hello.

623
00:39:28,115 --> 00:39:29,909
-Hello.
-Yes, hello.

624
00:39:29,992 --> 00:39:32,661
LOOKING FOR A NEW FACE
TO HOST JBC NEWS 8

625
00:39:33,371 --> 00:39:35,956
-He couldn't hold back?
-He should write an apology.

626
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:37,583
What's he going to do?

627
00:39:38,250 --> 00:39:40,252
He'll get fired at this rate.

628
00:39:41,253 --> 00:39:42,963
Hello, Mr. Kim.

629
00:39:43,047 --> 00:39:46,550
I'm back, as of today.
I apologize for causing you concern.

630
00:39:49,053 --> 00:39:50,054
What?

631
00:39:50,679 --> 00:39:53,265
What do you want?
Go do what you need to do.

632
00:39:53,349 --> 00:39:54,350
Yes, sir.

633
00:39:55,142 --> 00:39:58,229
He came to work? Wow, he's got thick skin.

634
00:39:58,312 --> 00:40:00,606
Those who should voluntarily resign
never do.

635
00:40:00,689 --> 00:40:02,691
Mr. Kim. I'm here.

636
00:40:04,402 --> 00:40:08,614
Hey, Mr. Choi! Give me a hug.

637
00:40:09,824 --> 00:40:10,825
So you're back?

638
00:40:10,908 --> 00:40:13,160
Yes, after completing my job
at the overseas branch.

639
00:40:13,244 --> 00:40:15,955
Nae-jeong, it's been so long.
You look great.

640
00:40:16,038 --> 00:40:18,165
I thought you were coming next month.
What a surprise.

641
00:40:18,249 --> 00:40:19,083
Plans changed.

642
00:40:19,166 --> 00:40:20,584
-Let's sit down.
-Welcome back.

643
00:40:20,668 --> 00:40:22,795
-You need a chair.
-I brought you something small.

644
00:40:22,878 --> 00:40:25,423
You didn't have to get me anything.
Oh, cookies?

645
00:40:25,506 --> 00:40:27,466
I didn't have time
to pick out proper gifts.

646
00:40:27,550 --> 00:40:30,261
-Guys, eat up. They're all cookies.
-Have a seat.

647
00:40:30,344 --> 00:40:33,973
-Open this and have a taste.
-Sure.

648
00:40:34,056 --> 00:40:35,766
So, how have you been?

649
00:40:35,850 --> 00:40:38,269
-I've been well.
-So you're back for good?

650
00:40:38,352 --> 00:40:40,187
-Yeah.
-Not going someplace else?

651
00:40:40,271 --> 00:40:41,272
Where?

652
00:40:41,939 --> 00:40:44,483
This makes me so happy, seriously.

653
00:40:44,984 --> 00:40:46,777
ANNOUNCER SONG KI-BAEK

654
00:40:46,861 --> 00:40:48,279
SONG KI-BAEK: SUSPENDED

655
00:40:55,744 --> 00:40:58,706
We'll start drinking in broad daylight
and drink until we drop.

656
00:40:59,457 --> 00:41:00,583
-I'm done for the day.
-Okay.

657
00:41:00,666 --> 00:41:02,751
-Have a great time.
-Join us if you can.

658
00:41:02,835 --> 00:41:04,920
-What shall we eat?
-Pork bone soup would be nice.

659
00:41:05,004 --> 00:41:06,922
Pork bone soup, it is.

660
00:41:10,843 --> 00:41:13,387
JBC NEWS 8 ANCHOR AUDITION

661
00:41:22,855 --> 00:41:25,733
He came to work? Wow, he's got thick skin.

662
00:41:25,816 --> 00:41:28,486
Those who should voluntarily resign
never do.

663
00:41:28,569 --> 00:41:30,279
-What?
-He came to work?

664
00:41:30,362 --> 00:41:32,114
-He's really something.
-Way to go.

665
00:41:32,198 --> 00:41:34,283
What's he going to do if he gets fired?

666
00:41:34,366 --> 00:41:36,619
-He's brazen.
-If I were him, I wouldn't come.

667
00:41:36,702 --> 00:41:38,162
Go do what you need to do.

668
00:42:07,650 --> 00:42:08,817
Mr. Song Ki-baek.

669
00:42:12,112 --> 00:42:14,198
You're breaking out in a cold sweat.

670
00:42:14,698 --> 00:42:15,991
Are you all right?

671
00:42:17,868 --> 00:42:20,371
Hey. I asked you if you were all right.

672
00:42:24,583 --> 00:42:25,709
Come on in.

673
00:42:27,294 --> 00:42:28,295
Over here.

674
00:42:29,380 --> 00:42:30,839
Come this way.

675
00:42:31,632 --> 00:42:34,176
Wait, can we come in here
without permission?

676
00:42:34,260 --> 00:42:37,346
There's no shoot until the evening,
so it's fine. Sit here.

677
00:42:37,429 --> 00:42:38,639
Okay.

678
00:42:39,473 --> 00:42:40,599
You can't stay here.

679
00:42:40,683 --> 00:42:42,268
We have to change the desks.

680
00:42:42,351 --> 00:42:44,895
Oh, you have to change the desks today.

681
00:42:45,813 --> 00:42:47,064
Come here. It's okay.

682
00:42:53,320 --> 00:42:55,322
They definitely don't need this set today.

683
00:42:55,406 --> 00:42:56,949
We have to dismantle the set.

684
00:42:57,491 --> 00:42:59,952
Oh, that's why they're dismantling it.

685
00:43:00,744 --> 00:43:03,372
Well, come with me.
I know of another studio.

686
00:43:16,176 --> 00:43:17,886
About yesterday. What was that?

687
00:43:17,970 --> 00:43:20,472
You said you'd figured out something
but made no sense.

688
00:43:20,973 --> 00:43:21,974
It was nothing.

689
00:43:23,892 --> 00:43:25,894
-Do I have food on my face?
-Nope.

690
00:43:27,646 --> 00:43:30,190
I do. Why did you lie?

691
00:43:31,775 --> 00:43:35,321
I guess you feel like your normal self,
seeing how you can lie like that.

692
00:43:39,617 --> 00:43:41,952
-Thanks for the food.
-You barely touched it.

693
00:43:42,036 --> 00:43:44,121
I have to go. Throw this out for me.

694
00:43:47,374 --> 00:43:48,375
Mr. Song.

695
00:43:49,418 --> 00:43:51,545
Just sit down for a moment.

696
00:43:54,173 --> 00:43:57,009
Maybe it's not a bad thing
that you've become so honest.

697
00:43:57,092 --> 00:43:59,053
It could be helpful for you.

698
00:43:59,136 --> 00:44:02,264
The moment the switch turns on,
I turn into a ticking time bomb.

699
00:44:04,016 --> 00:44:06,810
But does that "switch" really exist?

700
00:44:06,894 --> 00:44:08,062
Is it turned on now?

701
00:44:10,105 --> 00:44:11,148
I think it's off.

702
00:44:11,231 --> 00:44:12,816
But you're so honest right now.

703
00:44:12,900 --> 00:44:16,528
You already saw everything.
I don't need to hide it from you.

704
00:44:17,154 --> 00:44:18,155
Oh, right.

705
00:44:19,782 --> 00:44:20,949
You know…

706
00:44:23,160 --> 00:44:26,747
Do you think I can host a news show?
I mean, in this state.

707
00:44:27,873 --> 00:44:31,585
A news show? That might be a little too…

708
00:44:32,169 --> 00:44:33,587
Right?

709
00:44:36,048 --> 00:44:37,049
You see,

710
00:44:38,509 --> 00:44:42,763
I've put up with everything and held out
until now to be a news anchor.

711
00:44:44,640 --> 00:44:47,267
There were so many false rumors about me,

712
00:44:48,394 --> 00:44:49,603
and I used them

713
00:44:50,229 --> 00:44:53,857
because I wanted everyone to think
that position was rightfully mine.

714
00:44:59,488 --> 00:45:02,533
Ki-baek, what does the news mean to you?

715
00:45:10,624 --> 00:45:12,709
To me, it means…

716
00:45:20,426 --> 00:45:21,677
I'm not sure.

717
00:45:24,847 --> 00:45:27,266
I have to go. I'm sorry.

718
00:45:28,225 --> 00:45:29,476
Ki-baek.

719
00:45:32,396 --> 00:45:34,231
I don't really know what's going on,

720
00:45:34,731 --> 00:45:37,317
but I do know you're going through a lot.

721
00:45:38,485 --> 00:45:41,822
But if you let yourself get depressed,
it'll only make things worse.

722
00:45:41,905 --> 00:45:44,408
You have to cheer yourself up
during tough times.

723
00:45:44,491 --> 00:45:45,492
Okay?

724
00:45:47,661 --> 00:45:50,831
I'm struggling because I've got no energy,
but I'm supposed to cheer up?

725
00:45:54,209 --> 00:45:57,004
You know what self-defense is.
Protecting yourself physically.

726
00:45:57,087 --> 00:46:00,382
But do you know what's more important
and powerful than that?

727
00:46:01,467 --> 00:46:03,385
The art of protecting your heart.

728
00:46:04,303 --> 00:46:07,097
You must protect your own heart.

729
00:46:08,348 --> 00:46:09,725
"The art of protecting your heart"?

730
00:46:22,279 --> 00:46:24,323
-Is the team dinner at Bongbong Pub?
-Yes.

731
00:46:25,240 --> 00:46:28,160
But Mr. Kim said everyone
who reports to him should be there.

732
00:46:29,244 --> 00:46:30,579
Let's just go.

733
00:46:40,756 --> 00:46:43,509
BONGBONG? BONG…

734
00:46:58,106 --> 00:46:59,983
Hey, Song.

735
00:47:01,235 --> 00:47:04,154
I was going to call
but thought you might be here.

736
00:47:04,238 --> 00:47:05,280
And here you are.

737
00:47:24,216 --> 00:47:26,718
LOOKING FOR A NEW FACE
TO HOST JBC NEWS 8

738
00:47:35,018 --> 00:47:35,894
Hello.

739
00:47:35,978 --> 00:47:37,354
-Oh, hello.
-Hello.

740
00:47:37,854 --> 00:47:39,481
-Hi.
-Hello.

741
00:47:43,068 --> 00:47:44,069
Oh, Ki-baek--

742
00:47:47,030 --> 00:47:50,158
Look at you, Song Ki-baek. I knew it.

743
00:47:50,242 --> 00:47:53,120
He's trying to cheer himself up
even though he's got no energy.

744
00:47:53,203 --> 00:47:54,663
I should cheer up too!

745
00:47:56,873 --> 00:47:59,334
APPLICANT: SONG KI-BAEK
APPLYING FOR: JBC 8 NEWS ANCHOR

746
00:48:08,176 --> 00:48:09,928
Hey, Ki-baek. Come out.

747
00:48:11,346 --> 00:48:14,474
Did Mr. Kim tell you to audition?

748
00:48:14,558 --> 00:48:18,061
Rumors are running rampant
that Mr. Choi is getting the position.

749
00:48:18,145 --> 00:48:19,896
They asked rookie announcers to audition

750
00:48:19,980 --> 00:48:22,441
so it'd look like
they had enough applicants.

751
00:48:22,524 --> 00:48:23,734
What are you doing here?

752
00:48:24,693 --> 00:48:26,612
For God's sake, hey.

753
00:48:28,655 --> 00:48:31,658
It's a total shit show. It's all rigged.

754
00:48:31,742 --> 00:48:36,204
No one will say anything even if
you ditch the audition and leave now.

755
00:48:36,288 --> 00:48:38,498
Mr. Kim is just using you.

756
00:48:38,582 --> 00:48:40,375
-I know.
-Then why are you here?

757
00:48:40,459 --> 00:48:41,752
I must do this.

758
00:48:42,252 --> 00:48:46,465
I have to let him use me this time
to seize my next opportunity.

759
00:48:46,548 --> 00:48:48,508
Hey, Ki-baek.

760
00:48:48,592 --> 00:48:49,676
I will do it.

761
00:48:50,302 --> 00:48:51,303
I have to.

762
00:48:56,892 --> 00:48:58,602
Here for the audition, Ki-baek?

763
00:49:01,688 --> 00:49:03,982
-Let's both do our best.
-Yes.

764
00:49:12,366 --> 00:49:13,659
This way, please.

765
00:49:17,037 --> 00:49:17,954
-Hello.
-Hi.

766
00:49:18,038 --> 00:49:21,166
-Thank you.
-We're ready for the third applicant.

767
00:49:22,542 --> 00:49:23,835
Jin-ju, we need the script.

768
00:49:24,961 --> 00:49:26,004
Over here.

769
00:49:45,816 --> 00:49:47,859
Who's next?

770
00:49:47,943 --> 00:49:49,820
Number three, Song Ki-baek, is next.

771
00:49:49,903 --> 00:49:51,446
Song Ki-baek?

772
00:49:51,530 --> 00:49:52,656
NAME: SONG KI-BAEK

773
00:49:53,532 --> 00:49:55,784
Hey, isn't he

774
00:49:55,867 --> 00:49:57,577
that guy from JBC News at Noon?

775
00:49:58,078 --> 00:50:01,331
When I think about
what I had to do to clean up that mess…

776
00:50:01,415 --> 00:50:04,835
But I admit I laughed my head off
when I watched that clip afterward.

777
00:50:04,918 --> 00:50:06,753
Guess there weren't a lot of applicants.

778
00:50:06,837 --> 00:50:08,505
I just see a bunch of losers.

779
00:50:08,588 --> 00:50:10,966
Let's make this quick. Give him a cue.

780
00:50:28,650 --> 00:50:29,860
All right. Ready?

781
00:50:30,819 --> 00:50:32,404
Will you wait if I'm not ready?

782
00:50:34,614 --> 00:50:35,657
Pardon me?

783
00:50:37,576 --> 00:50:38,910
All right, ready.

784
00:50:44,791 --> 00:50:47,294
Hey, On Woo-ju.
You're going to make the floor collapse.

785
00:50:48,044 --> 00:50:51,256
Even when I start my morning feeling good,
it doesn't even last half a day.

786
00:50:53,258 --> 00:50:54,926
JBC NEWS 8 ANCHOR AUDITION

787
00:51:06,897 --> 00:51:08,315
Camera, we're rolling.

788
00:51:08,398 --> 00:51:10,233
You can start when you're ready.

789
00:51:12,652 --> 00:51:13,820
But seriously.

790
00:51:13,904 --> 00:51:16,281
Who told Song Ki-baek
he could participate in this?

791
00:51:16,364 --> 00:51:17,491
This is just embarrassing.

792
00:51:17,574 --> 00:51:19,117
Who's emb--

793
00:51:19,743 --> 00:51:23,371
-Embarrass…
-Come on. He can hear you.

794
00:51:23,455 --> 00:51:24,873
So what? Who cares?

795
00:51:24,956 --> 00:51:26,917
It's not like he'll get
the anchor position.

796
00:51:27,000 --> 00:51:29,711
Hey, let's make this quick.
Let's not waste our time.

797
00:51:30,587 --> 00:51:31,838
Who's embarrass--

798
00:51:32,506 --> 00:51:33,924
Embarrassing…

799
00:51:36,009 --> 00:51:37,093
Number three?

800
00:51:38,887 --> 00:51:40,806
You can start. Please start.

801
00:51:54,402 --> 00:51:55,612
One moment.

802
00:52:11,670 --> 00:52:13,296
The switch is turned on, isn't it?

803
00:52:16,258 --> 00:52:19,010
Neither of us knows how to turn it off,

804
00:52:19,094 --> 00:52:22,389
but I know that this audition is
very important to you.

805
00:52:23,932 --> 00:52:26,685
I asked you what the news meant
to you, remember?

806
00:52:26,768 --> 00:52:30,564
I think you're here because you know
the answer to my question.

807
00:52:34,067 --> 00:52:35,902
Remember the art of protecting your heart?

808
00:52:39,614 --> 00:52:40,824
Protect your heart.

809
00:52:40,907 --> 00:52:44,452
You're the only one here
who can protect yourself.

810
00:52:48,248 --> 00:52:49,249
Excuse me.

811
00:52:50,000 --> 00:52:51,835
Can't you see we're holding an audition?

812
00:52:51,918 --> 00:52:56,339
I'm sorry. I'm his stylist.
I just noticed that his tie was crooked.

813
00:52:56,965 --> 00:52:58,842
Sorry about that. All right.

814
00:52:58,925 --> 00:53:00,260
-Please get out.
-I'm sorry!

815
00:53:01,261 --> 00:53:02,637
One, two, one, two.

816
00:53:05,098 --> 00:53:07,893
Mr. Song. Do you want to continue?

817
00:53:08,518 --> 00:53:09,519
Yes.

818
00:53:10,896 --> 00:53:12,188
Get ready again.

819
00:53:32,375 --> 00:53:36,212
Good evening, ladies and gentlemen.
Welcome to JBC News.

820
00:53:37,172 --> 00:53:42,135
The National Human Rights Commission
and the Journalists Association of Korea

821
00:53:42,218 --> 00:53:44,763
co-published the 2023 Human Rights
Report Casebook.

822
00:53:44,846 --> 00:53:46,723
This was done in compliance

823
00:53:46,806 --> 00:53:49,351
with the Human Rights Practices
Reporting Standards,

824
00:53:49,434 --> 00:53:53,647
which were enacted in 2011 and amended
in 2014 by the two organizations.

825
00:53:53,730 --> 00:53:56,566
Since the COVID-19 pandemic,
standards on reporting infectious diseases

826
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:59,903
and human rights practices
have been strengthened…

827
00:53:59,986 --> 00:54:02,781
-Well, I must say, not bad.
-Right?

828
00:54:02,864 --> 00:54:06,368
It reflects the media's neutral gaze
on the reporting of sex work.

829
00:54:06,451 --> 00:54:09,788
The media outlets' heated competition
over viewership ratings has resulted

830
00:54:09,871 --> 00:54:13,124
in reckless reporting,
which has been an issue lately.

831
00:54:13,208 --> 00:54:14,960
All eyes are on whether

832
00:54:15,043 --> 00:54:18,004
the media's efforts to shift away
from such trends will be fruitful.

833
00:54:18,088 --> 00:54:20,840
Song Ki-baek, JBC News.

834
00:54:25,220 --> 00:54:27,222
We'll move on to the anchor briefing.

835
00:54:33,436 --> 00:54:34,980
NS-2 ANCHOR BRIEFING

836
00:54:35,772 --> 00:54:39,067
Why was Choi Nae-jeong suddenly summoned
from the overseas branch?

837
00:54:39,150 --> 00:54:42,362
The higher-ups flipped out
over the main news' rock-bottom ratings.

838
00:54:42,445 --> 00:54:45,824
Choi Nae-jeong has a huge fandom.
It all comes down to business.

839
00:54:46,574 --> 00:54:49,744
We need ads and better ratings.
The news must be marketable to be saved.

840
00:54:50,370 --> 00:54:51,621
Man.

841
00:54:51,705 --> 00:54:55,333
What happened to the honor
and dignity of the news?

842
00:54:55,417 --> 00:54:58,211
They all know
such things do not exist here.

843
00:54:58,294 --> 00:55:00,839
Actually, I bet they aren't
even interested.

844
00:55:01,423 --> 00:55:05,343
Look, that's why he volunteered
to be part of this shit show.

845
00:55:09,764 --> 00:55:12,976
Ki-baek, what do the news mean to you?

846
00:55:16,229 --> 00:55:18,523
To me, it means…

847
00:55:27,991 --> 00:55:29,993
A city with a beautiful name, Bangkok.

848
00:55:30,076 --> 00:55:32,454
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

849
00:55:32,954 --> 00:55:35,123
As adults,
it is our duty to protect children.

850
00:55:35,206 --> 00:55:38,001
And it's important to pay attention
in your day-to-day life.

851
00:55:42,839 --> 00:55:44,340
To me, the news is…

852
00:55:48,386 --> 00:55:52,640
In my life filled with lies,
it was the only real thing.

853
00:55:54,768 --> 00:55:56,644
Ki-baek, what do you want to be?

854
00:55:56,728 --> 00:55:59,022
You get good grades, you're popular.
I'm so jealous.

855
00:55:59,105 --> 00:56:00,690
How am I going to support myself?

856
00:56:00,774 --> 00:56:02,275
Ki-baek isn't like you.

857
00:56:02,358 --> 00:56:03,943
I'm sure he already has a plan.

858
00:56:04,611 --> 00:56:06,446
Hey, Ki-baek, what do you want to be?

859
00:56:10,033 --> 00:56:11,326
Announcer.

860
00:56:12,410 --> 00:56:14,245
I want to be an announcer.

861
00:56:14,329 --> 00:56:16,831
NEW ANNOUNCER TRAINING
IN SESSION

862
00:56:19,667 --> 00:56:24,297
I sincerely promise you that I'll only
report the truth and never lie to you.

863
00:56:24,380 --> 00:56:26,758
Song Ki-baek, JBC.

864
00:56:29,052 --> 00:56:30,887
Here, I don't have to lie.

865
00:56:31,471 --> 00:56:33,848
No, I must not lie.

866
00:56:46,528 --> 00:56:50,782
NS-2 ANCHOR BRIEFING

867
00:57:11,886 --> 00:57:15,598
I cannot lie.

868
00:57:17,767 --> 00:57:20,186
Truth, fairness and justice.

869
00:57:20,270 --> 00:57:23,606
I trust that news programs devoid
of these values aren't worth existing.

870
00:57:28,445 --> 00:57:33,366
That is the reason I must be
a man who cannot lie,

871
00:57:34,868 --> 00:57:38,788
and the reason why I've decided
to leave this corrupt news studio

872
00:57:38,872 --> 00:57:41,583
that reeks
of such a disgusting, rotten stench…

873
00:57:43,751 --> 00:57:45,545
which I cannot stand any longer.

874
00:58:10,904 --> 00:58:12,822
Let go of me! What did you say?

875
00:58:12,906 --> 00:58:14,908
I let a loser like you audition, and what?

876
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:16,993
What's rotten? What stench?

877
00:58:17,076 --> 00:58:18,536
You little…

878
00:58:24,167 --> 00:58:25,210
What?

879
00:58:28,213 --> 00:58:29,547
You.

880
00:58:31,674 --> 00:58:32,675
You stink.

881
00:58:37,138 --> 00:58:38,598
You rude bastard!

882
00:58:39,807 --> 00:58:40,642
Oh, no.

883
00:59:00,537 --> 00:59:02,330
Where do you think you're going?

884
00:59:02,413 --> 00:59:04,582
Hey! You little…

885
00:59:04,666 --> 00:59:06,334
If you leave now, you'll get fired.

886
00:59:06,417 --> 00:59:07,460
Woo-ju.

887
00:59:08,503 --> 00:59:11,589
Today, my heart and my dream…

888
00:59:12,423 --> 00:59:13,883
I managed to protect both.

889
00:59:19,347 --> 00:59:20,974
"The art of protecting your heart."

890
00:59:23,226 --> 00:59:24,352
Thank you.

891
00:59:29,566 --> 00:59:32,318
Un-baek, don't let it drop like that.

892
00:59:32,402 --> 00:59:35,238
Here, like this. Taekwon!

893
00:59:35,321 --> 00:59:36,864
-Now you try.
-Taekwon!

894
00:59:36,948 --> 00:59:39,784
-Okay. Pow!
-Pow!

895
00:59:39,867 --> 00:59:42,245
I knew it. You are a genius. Well done.

896
00:59:43,621 --> 00:59:45,039
-Mom!
-Mom.

897
00:59:46,916 --> 00:59:48,793
Mom, want me to teach you too?

898
00:59:48,876 --> 00:59:50,003
No, thank you.

899
00:59:50,587 --> 00:59:55,675
Mom, I will protect you, Dad
and Un-baek once I get my red belt.

900
00:59:57,760 --> 01:00:00,513
Self-defense moves.
My master said he'd teach me those too.

901
01:00:00,597 --> 01:00:01,723
Gosh, you.

902
01:00:01,806 --> 01:00:03,308
Self-defense moves!

903
01:00:04,726 --> 01:00:10,773
You see, before you become
someone who is physically strong,

904
01:00:11,899 --> 01:00:14,193
I want you to be someone
who's mentally strong.

905
01:00:14,277 --> 01:00:16,529
It's important
to protect yourself physically,

906
01:00:16,613 --> 01:00:20,742
but protecting your heart
is more difficult, and it's more precious.

907
01:00:24,912 --> 01:00:27,332
I will protect your heart.

908
01:00:28,875 --> 01:00:30,084
Your heart.

909
01:00:31,753 --> 01:00:33,171
I'll protect your heart too.

910
01:00:33,254 --> 01:00:35,256
Goodness, my babies.

911
01:00:36,007 --> 01:00:39,135
All right. Ki-baek, Un-baek.
You can do it.

912
01:00:39,218 --> 01:00:40,219
Yes, we can do it!

913
01:00:40,303 --> 01:00:41,304
-We can do it!
-Yes!

914
01:00:41,387 --> 01:00:42,388
We can do it.

915
01:00:44,140 --> 01:00:46,684
-Let's go.
-Let's eat something delicious at home.

916
01:00:46,768 --> 01:00:49,020
Okay, we'll have a nice dinner.

917
01:01:00,365 --> 01:01:02,742
ANNOUNCER SONG KI-BAEK

918
01:01:20,927 --> 01:01:22,845
FRANKLY SPEAKING

919
01:01:23,638 --> 01:01:25,181
It was cool how you left.

920
01:01:25,264 --> 01:01:27,934
I've never seen anything like it.

921
01:01:28,017 --> 01:01:31,521
Throw your shoulders back
and always talk with confidence.

922
01:01:31,604 --> 01:01:33,022
Wait, hold on.

923
01:01:33,106 --> 01:01:36,776
You'll starve to death
trying to protect your dream.

924
01:01:36,859 --> 01:01:38,736
I knew you had it in you, Woo-ju.

925
01:01:38,820 --> 01:01:40,738
How did you get
Kim Jeong-heon just like that?

926
01:01:40,822 --> 01:01:42,115
What's your deal with Kim Jeong-heon?

927
01:01:42,198 --> 01:01:43,241
Ms. On Woo-ju.

928
01:01:43,991 --> 01:01:46,577
-Lately Woo-ju seems…
-You're worried, right?

929
01:01:47,912 --> 01:01:49,497
That was a close call.

930
01:01:49,580 --> 01:01:51,749
Why is his phone off?

931
01:01:51,833 --> 01:01:53,292
-Where were you?
-Where were you?

932
01:01:53,376 --> 01:01:55,878
Let's give this a shot.

933
01:01:58,339 --> 01:02:03,344
Subtitle translation by: Liya Choi

